# CodeTracer local environment overrides.
#
# This file is a TEMPLATE — copy it to .env and uncomment the variables
# you want to enable.  The .envrc loads .env via dotenv_if_exists, so
# direnv (and any tool reached through `direnv exec` / `just`) picks
# them up automatically.
#
# .env is intentionally NOT checked in.  Local overrides stay local.
#
# Default behaviour (everything below commented out): unchanged — the
# normal GPU/display-driver code paths are exercised, exactly as on
# developer workstations with real hardware.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Visual Replay — software-only GL/EGL on hosts without a usable GPU
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# CodeTracer's visual replay integration test (`visual-replay-real-recording.spec.ts`)
# records a small GL fixture and replays it through `ct_gfx_player`.  On a
# host with no 3D-capable GPU (e.g. a server with a Matrox / BMC console
# graphics chip, or a container without /dev/dri/render*), the record and
# replay stages need Mesa's software rasterizer (llvmpipe) configured
# explicitly.
#
# Set `CODETRACER_VISUAL_REPLAY_SOFTWARE_GL=1` to opt in.  When unset
# (the default), the test harness does NOT touch any of these variables
# — real-GPU coverage is never silently disabled.
#
# CODETRACER_VISUAL_REPLAY_SOFTWARE_GL=1
#
# Mesa root path.  Required when CODETRACER_VISUAL_REPLAY_SOFTWARE_GL=1.
# The harness derives LIBGL_DRIVERS_PATH, LD_LIBRARY_PATH, and
# __EGL_VENDOR_LIBRARY_DIRS from this single root, so you only need to
# update it when Mesa is bumped in the nix flake.
#
# Find the active Mesa derivation with:
#   ls /nix/store/ | grep -E '^[a-z0-9]{32}-mesa-[0-9]' | sort | tail -1
#
# CODETRACER_MESA_ROOT=/nix/store/<hash>-mesa-X.Y.Z
#
# Recorder checkpoint interval (ms).  Defaults to 250 ms, which is enough
# headroom for the gl_scene fixture under llvmpipe.  Lower it if you see
# `error: failed to finalize trace: twFull` on more event-heavy fixtures;
# raise it if startup overhead dominates on simpler ones.
#
# CODETRACER_VISUAL_REPLAY_RECORDER_CHECKPOINT_MS=250

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Pre-recorded visual trace (skip the gl_scene record step entirely)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Point at an existing .ct trace that already carries the four visual
# replay artifacts (gfx_commands.dat, gfx_bulkdata.dat, gfx_commands.idx,
# gfx_frames.idx) in `<trace>/gfx_stream/`.  Useful for CI hosts that
# cannot record GL traces at all, or for reproducing a known regression.
#
# Setting this bypasses both the gl_scene build and the ct_cli record
# step, so the software-GL variables above are not needed (only the
# replay player needs EGL, and that needs software-GL too if no GPU).
#
# CODETRACER_REAL_VISUAL_TRACE=/absolute/path/to/recorded.ct
